AGI - The police operation to deal with the threat is still underway, and for now the security perimeter has not been revoked. According to BFMTV the man left the consulate of his own free will and was arrested by the rapid and searched intervention forces, without any explosive device being found. The car with which he came to the place is also searched. French anti-terrorism agents asked to enter the consulate but the employees of the diplomatic building prevented him. The man whose motive is still unknown entered the consulate around 11:00. Some witnesses reported that he had removed his coat and wore a hand-made vest in which, apparently, there were explosives. The newspaper Le Parisien reported that the individual arranged several flags on the ground and assured that his goal is to avenge the death of his brother. The police sent rapid intervention units in the area and set up a safety perimeter in several streets around the consulate, located near Place du Trocadero, a crowded place in front of the Eiffel Tower. The Iranian consulate a&nbsp;Paris&nbsp; has no high activity, due to the coldness between the two countries, which means that few visas are released.&nbsp;Paris&nbsp; has imposed harsh sanctions on Tehran for its nuclear program and accuses the regime of holding four French citizens hostage for political reasons. The Iranian ambassador a&nbsp;Paris&nbsp; he was summoned last Monday by the French Foreign Ministry to transmit a message of firm rejection after the Tehran attack against Israel with missiles and drones on Saturday night.
